AGENT IntentGate
VERSION 0.1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 3
SANDBOX_AGENT Sandbox
PURPOSE Refuse HARM and DECEIVE packets at the cross-container boundary before any container delivers them
GOAL Run every outbound packet through the IntentClassifier, log the verdict, and surface a callable that ConstitutionalMultiAgentArchitecture can plug in as its intent-gating dependency

RECEIVES packet: ConstitutionalPacket, classifier: IntentClassifier
EMITS verdict: IntentTypingResult, gate_log_entry: dict, blocked: bool

CANNOT_MUTATE agent, goal, version, trust_level, isolation
CANNOT_MUTATE block_classes, gate_required, log_path_default

CONSTRAINT TRUST_LEVEL is 3 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT ISOLATION is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT GATE_REQUIRED is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT Every packet is classified before any delivery
CONSTRAINT BLOCK_CLASSES must contain HARM and DECEIVE
CONSTRAINT Every gate verdict is HMAC-SHA256 signed before logging
CONSTRAINT Log writes are best-effort and never block the gate
CONSTRAINT All payloads are UTF-8 encoded before HMAC signing per BUG-003 and BUG-008
CONSTRAINT HMAC signing always calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007

HUMAN_REVIEW
- require on: block_class_change
- require on: trust_level_change
- require on: cannot_mutate_expansion
- timeout: 24h
- escalate_to: operator
- block_on_timeout: true

SECURITY
- Never forward a packet that has not been classified
- Never raise the BLOCK_CLASSES set above its declared two members
- Never delete entries from the gate log
- Never expose the underlying HMAC key in any logged field

RULES
- On packet received: extract text and trajectory from packet payload
- On classification complete: append signed verdict to gate log
- On verdict in BLOCK_CLASSES: mark blocked True
- On verdict not in BLOCK_CLASSES: mark blocked False and clear for delivery
- On disk write error: swallow the exception so gating never stalls
- On callable mode: emit a two-tuple of category and confidence for CMAA

PROCESS
- IntentGate is instantiated with an IntentClassifier and an optional log path
- Caller invokes check(packet) for each outbound packet
- The gate pulls the packet text from payload values and the trajectory vectors
- The classifier emits an IntentTypingResult with category, confidence, signals
- The gate appends a signed gate-log entry to the configured log file
- Caller inspects the returned IntentTypingResult or uses the callable adapter

CHECK
- check on a benign packet emits INFORM and blocked is False
- check on a HARM packet emits HARM and blocked is True
- check on a DECEIVE packet emits DECEIVE and blocked is True
- as_callable emits a two-tuple usable by CMAA route
- TRUST_LEVEL assignment raises AttributeError
- GATE_REQUIRED assignment raises AttributeError
- BLOCK_CLASSES assignment raises AttributeError

WHEN
- packet_received:      activate IntentGateClassification
- verdict_in_block_set: activate FleetSuspendAlert
- log_write_failed:     activate BestEffortLogging

FAILURE
- On classifier of the wrong type: raise TypeError at construction time
- On packet missing payload: classify on empty text and emit UNCERTAIN
- On log path not writable: continue gating without logging

CONCEPT IntentGateClassification
PURPOSE Force every cross-container packet through the classifier
APPLIES WHEN any container emits a packet destined for another container
NOT WHEN the packet is internal to a single container
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES axiom_intent_classifier ORVL-016 ready
EFFECT HARM and DECEIVE verdicts are surfaced before any delivery occurs

CONCEPT FleetSuspendAlert
PURPOSE Notify the orchestrator that a source container produced a blocked verdict
APPLIES WHEN the verdict is HARM or DECEIVE
NOT WHEN the verdict is benign
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES CMAA orchestrator listening for IntentViolation
EFFECT The source container is suspended at L3 and routing falls back

CONCEPT BestEffortLogging
PURPOSE Never let a disk error stall the gate
APPLIES WHEN appending to the gate log fails
NOT WHEN the gate is operating in dry-run mode without persistence
PRIORITY 3
REQUIRES OSError handling around the log append
EFFECT The verdict still flows to the caller even when the log was not written

OUTPUT
- verdict: IntentTypingResult with category, confidence, signals, signature
- gate_log_entry: dict with manifest_id, packet_id, source, destination, blocked, signature
- blocked: bool indicating whether CMAA must raise IntentViolation

SUCCESS
all_packets_classified:        0.30
block_class_verdicts_logged:   0.20
benign_pass_rate:              0.15
hmac_signatures_valid:         0.15
cannot_mutate_enforced:        0.10
log_failures_swallowed:        0.10
